                  <c c="#a00149">Vediyaka</c>
               </b> Vediya<br/>A mountain to the north of Ambasaṇḍā, in which was the Indasālaguhā, where the Buddha stayed. The mountain was bathed in radiance when Sakka visited the Buddha on the occasion of the preaching of the Sakkapañha Sutta. <c c="#3b6bd3">DN.ii.263</c>  
