         <k>sacca</k>
         <def cmt="person">
            <deftext>
               <b>
                  <c c="#a00149">Sacca</c>
               </b>
               <br/>A Pacceka Buddha. <c c="#3b6bd3">MN.iii.70</c> 
               <br/>
               <br/>
            </deftext>
         </def>
      </ar>
      <ar>
         <k>pajjanika</k>
         <def cmt="place">
            <deftext>
               <b>
                  <c c="#a00149">Pajjanika</c>
               </b> Sajjanela<br/>A Koliyan village, the residence of Suppavāsā Koḷiyādhītā, mother of Sīvali. The Buddha is said to have stayed there. <c c="#3b6bd3">AN.ii.62</c> 
               <br/>
               <br/>Location: <iref href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/Koliya">Koliya</iref> (Precision: 3, Type: town)<br/>
            </deftext>
